file.name: zendesk.yaml
file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        allow_attachments: {type: string}
        assignee_id: {type: string}
        brand_id: {type: string}
        collaborator_ids: {type: string}
        created_at: {type: string}
        custom_fields: {type: string}
        description: {type: string}
        due_at: {type: string}
        external_id: {type: string}
        fields: {type: string}
        forum_topic_id: {type: string}
        group_id: {type: string}
        has_incidents: {type: string}
        id: {type: string}
        is_public: {type: string}
        organization_id: {type: string}
        priority: {type: string}
        problem_id: {type: string}
        raw_subject: {type: string}
        recipient: {type: string}
        requester_id: {type: string}
        satisfaction_rating: {type: string}
        sharing_agreement_ids: {type: string}
        status: {type: string}
        subject: {type: string}
        submitter_id: {type: string}
        tags: {type: string}
        type: {type: string}
        updated_at: {type: string}
        url: {type: string}
        via_channel: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        errorMessage: {type: string}
        successful: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp2:
      properties:
        content: {type: string}
        id: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes: {}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of Zendesk Zendesk
  title: Zendesk Zendesk
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Zendesk Create Ticket
      parameters:
      - description: The agent currently assigned to the ticket.
        example: '1234'
        in: body
        name: Assignee ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Enterprise only. The id of the brand this ticket is associated
          with.
        example: '1234'
        in: body
        name: Brand ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Comma-separated list of ID's of users currently CC'd on the ticket.
        example: 123,456,789
        in: query
        name: Collaborator IDs
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: When this record was created.
        example: '2018-02-12T18:30:12'
        in: query
        name: Created At
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Description of the ticket.
        example: This is my description.
        in: query
        name: Description
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: If this is a ticket of type 'task' it has a due date. Due date
          format uses ISO 8601 format.
        example: '2019-12-25T13:37:00'
        in: query
        name: Due At
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: An ID you can use to link Zendesk Support tickets to local records.
        example: '1234'
        in: body
        name: External ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The topic this ticket originated from, if any.
        example: '1234'
        in: body
        name: Forum Topic ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The group this ticket is assigned to.
        example: '1234'
        in: body
        name: Group ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Is true if this ticket has been marked as a problem, false otherwise.
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Has Incidents
        required: false
        schema: {type: boolean}
      - description: The organization of the requester. You can only specify the ID
          of an organization associated with the requester. See Organization Memberships.
        example: '1234'
        in: body
        name: Organization ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'The urgency with which the ticket should be addressed. Possible
          values: ''urgent'', ''high'', ''normal'', ''low''.'
        example: high
        in: query
        name: Priority
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: For tickets of type 'incident', the ID of the problem the incident
          is linked to.
        example: '1234'
        in: body
        name: Problem ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The dynamic content placeholder, if present, or the 'subject'
          value, if not. See Dynamic Content.
        example: My Raw Subject
        in: query
        name: Raw Subject
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The original recipient e-mail address of the ticket.
        example: john.smith@company.com
        in: query
        name: Recipient
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The user who requested this ticket.
        example: '1234'
        in: body
        name: Requester ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Comma-separated list of ID's of the sharing agreements used for
          this ticket.
        example: 123,456,789
        in: query
        name: Sharing Agreement IDs
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'The state of the ticket. Possible values: ''new'', ''open'',
          ''pending'', ''hold'', ''solved'', ''closed''.'
        example: open
        in: query
        name: Status
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The value of the subject field for this ticket.
        example: My Subject
        in: query
        name: Subject
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The user who submitted the ticket. The submitter always becomes
          the author of the first comment on the ticket.
        example: '1234'
        in: body
        name: Submitter ID
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: 'The type of this ticket. Possible values: ''problem'', ''incident'',
          ''question'' or ''task''.'
        example: incident
        in: query
        name: Type
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: When this record last got updated.
        example: '2019-01-15T22:45:00'
        in: query
        name: Updated At
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Zendesk Create Ticket
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Zendesk Delete Ticket
      parameters:
      - description: The ID of the ticket to be deleted
        example: '123'
        in: body
        name: ID
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Zendesk Delete Ticket
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: Zendesk Search by Sender
      parameters:
      - description: The sender whose instances are being searched for
        example: someone@gmail.com
        in: query
        name: Sender
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: The recipient who is being searched for
        example: support@subdomain.zendesk.com
        in: query
        name: Recipient
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Zendesk Search by Sender
tags:
- {name: Ticket Management}

Error: parse: parse spec: paths: tmp0: post: operation "": parameters: parse parameter "Assignee ID": unsupported parameter type "body"
